        "title": "fix(agent): load shared tools bootstrap instructions",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Auto-load `TOOLS_SHARED.md` as an optional workspace bootstrap file.\n- Route `TOOLS_SHARED.md` through Codex inherited developer instructions alongside `TOOLS.md`.\n- Allow the intended workspace-local symlink shape: `<agent>/TOOLS_SHARED.md -> ../shared/TOOLS.md`, while rejecting other sibling targets.\n- Document the public bootstrap surface, subagent/cron context behavior, bootstrap-extra-files behavior, and the exact sibling symlink exception.\n\n## Compatibility and security-boundary intent\n\nThis PR intentionally adds a new optional workspace bootstrap file surface. Existing workspaces that already contain `TOOLS_SHARED.md`, or the exact supported sibling symlink `<agent-workspace>/TOOLS_SHARED.md -> ../shared/TOOLS.md`, will start injecting that file after upgrade.\n\nThe cross-workspace read exception is intentionally narrow: it only applies to `TOOLS_SHARED.md`, only accepts the sibling shared target `../shared/TOOLS.md` after realpath comparison, and continues to reject other sibling workspace targets. This preserves the workspace-root read boundary while supporting the documented multi-agent shared-tools layout.\n\n`TOOLS_SHARED.md` follows the same lifetime class as `TOOLS.md`: native Codex receives both as inherited developer instructions, subagents receive `AGENTS.md`/`TOOLS.md`/`TOOLS_SHARED.md`, and cron sessions include `TOOLS_SHARED.md` alongside the existing cron bootstrap allowlist.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Workspace bootstrap now loads a workspace-local `TOOLS_SHARED.md` entry so an agent can combine its own `TOOLS.md` with shared tool guidance.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout with a redacted agent workspace using the intended `TOOLS_SHARED.md -> ../shared/TOOLS.md` symlink shape. No channel credentials or provider API keys were used.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Ran a local loader probe against the redacted workspace after applying this patch.\n- Evidence after fix: Copied live command output with machine/user paths and file content redacted:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"workspaceDir\": \"<agent-workspace>\",\n  \"link\": \"TOOLS_SHARED.md\",\n  \"symlinkTarget\": \"../shared/TOOLS.md\",\n  \"loaded\": true,\n  \"loadedName\": \"TOOLS_SHARED.md\",\n  \"loadedPath\": \"<agent-workspace>/TOOLS_SHARED.md\",\n  \"contentPresent\": true\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: `loadWorkspaceBootstrapFiles()` returned `TOOLS_SHARED.md` as loaded from the workspace-local symlink path, with content present and without exposing the shared file content.\n- What was not tested: No full live Codex model turn was sent; this proof covers the workspace bootstrap loader behavior changed by this PR.\n\n## Validation\n\nAfter rebasing onto current `origin/main`:\n\n- `pnpm check:docs`\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm prompt:snapshots:check`\n- `pnpm vitest run src/agents/workspace.test.ts src/agents/bootstrap-files.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts test/scripts/prompt-snapshots.test.ts -- --runInBand` — 6 files / 268 tests passed\n- `pnpm vitest run src/agents/workspace.load-extra-bootstrap-files.test.ts src/hooks/bundled/bootstrap-extra-files/handler.test.ts -- --runInBand` — 3 files / 16 tests passed\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/codex/src/app-server/attempt-context.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts src/agents/workspace.ts src/agents/workspace.test.ts src/agents/bootstrap-files.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.ts test/helpers/agents/happy-path-prompt-snapshots.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/codex/src/app-server/attempt-context.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts src/agents/workspace.ts src/agents/workspace.test.ts src/agents/bootstrap-files.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.ts test/helpers/agents/happy-path-prompt-snapshots.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nNote: a local full `pnpm lint:core` run on the rebased branch reported three `no-unnecessary-type-assertion` findings in `src/commands/test-runtime-config-helpers.ts`, outside this PR's changed files. Changed-file oxlint for this PR's source/test files passed.\n",
